******
[4]
Date: Wed 2 Dec 2009
Source: My News [edited]
<http://www.mynews.in/News/State_police_file_FIR_in_Kaiga_tritium_contamination_case_N31719.html#>


State police file FIR [first information report] in Kaiga tritium
contamination case
----------------------------------------------------------------------
The Karnataka police today[2 Dec 2009] filed an FIR in the case
relating to alleged mixing of highly radioactive tritium in drinking
water cooler at the nuclear power plant at the Kaiga Atomic Power
Station (KAPS).

With the filing of the FIR the state police joined the sleuths of
Intelligence Bureau (IB) and Nuclear Power Corporation India Limited
(NCPIL) to identify the culprits behind the incident.

Uttara Kannada district police chief, Mr Raman Gupta, informed
newspersons that the FIR was filed following a formal complaint from
the authorities of KAPS about the mixing of tritium on 23 and 24 Nov
2009. He said the district police have also taken up investigation to
nab the culprits.

He said the FIR had not mentioned any names. However, the
investigating team headed by deputy superintendent of police, would
look into all angles including the possibility of the theft of tritium.

--
